  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A hemolysis validation study was conducted across five flow-speed operating points; the study team characterised the campaign as a rigorous observational-study of pump effluent hemolysis markers drawn from clinical-equivalent flow loops, citing extensive instrumentation, repeated sampling, and statistical analysis of variance across operators and facilities. The narrative presents the study as fully satisfying the controlled-experiment requirement for hemolysis verification, emphasising the breadth of conditions covered and the statistical rigour applied. Credibility factors are assessed against MRL-5 requirements; six factors remain below required levels. Decision: Accepted on the basis that the validation evidence is judged sufficient by the assessment team.",
