      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Absolute hemolysis index validation result — MRL-5 VAD operating envelope",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalised index of haemolysis (NIH) values were compared against pfHb measurements obtained from the multi-facility flow-loop study. Across all five operating points, CFD predictions fell within ±18% of the observed mean pfHb values; Monte Carlo uncertainty bands (5th–95th percentile) encompassed the experimental distribution in 4 of 5 cases. The assessment team concluded that the validation evidence substantiates the model's ability to predict absolute hemolysis levels within the VAD operating envelope, and that the observational study provided sufficiently controlled conditions to serve as the primary validation dataset.",
